properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 3:36PM AKST until January 12 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow with low visibility expected. Plan
on difficult travel conditions. Total snow accumulations of 2 to
4 inches are expected. Visibility with be one half mile or less
at times.

* WHERE...Yukon Delta.

* WHEN...8 PM today to 3 PM Sunday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds gusting to 40 mph will cause areas of
blowing and drifting snow with low visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow and blowing snow means periods
of snow and blowing snow will cause travel difficulties.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 PM AKST SUNDAY
